Final: final keyword is used to define an entity which cannot be changed.
	final class: a class can not be inherited
	final method: method that cannot be overrided or will be hidden by subsclasses
	final variable: can only be initialized once, either via an initializer or an assignment statement. 
	
	
Finally: a keyword define an logic block, usually follow the try block, to ensure the exist of the try block.
	finally block is executed even if unexpected exception has occurs. finally is useful for more than just 
	exception handling â€” it allows the programmer to avoid having cleanup code accidentally bypassed by a return, 
	continue, or break. Putting cleanup code in a finally block is always a good practice, even when no exceptions 
	are anticipated.